00:16:59,716 --> 00:17:01,876
She says she's not coming.

271
00:17:02,584 --> 00:17:04,185
Why's she so willful?

272
00:17:04,185 --> 00:17:06,265
We had plans.

273
00:17:07,390 --> 00:17:08,890
Lin's so excellent.

274
00:17:08,890 --> 00:17:12,498
How does he even put up with her?

275
00:17:12,498 --> 00:17:15,001
Shame. Such a shame.

276
00:17:15,001 --> 00:17:16,852
This kid...

277
00:17:16,852 --> 00:17:18,332
Xue Jiao's amazing, too.

278
00:17:18,332 --> 00:17:19,687
Here.

279
00:17:19,687 --> 00:17:21,787
Shut your mouth!

280
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:25,240
Lin, the next deal will be done later.

281
00:17:25,240 --> 00:17:27,566
You wanna go celebrate tonight?

282
00:17:27,566 --> 00:17:29,102
Call your sister, too.

283
00:17:29,102 --> 00:17:31,340
It's probably not that easy.

284
00:17:31,340 --> 00:17:32,625
It's a done deal.

285
00:17:32,625 --> 00:17:34,705
What's there to worry about?

286
00:17:36,857 --> 00:17:39,900
So that's the situation.

287
00:17:39,900 --> 00:17:42,210
C1 didn't pass our tech department's inspection.

288
00:17:42,210 --> 00:17:44,460
I'm really sorry about that.

289
00:17:44,460 --> 00:17:47,140
Can we see the acceptance report?

290
00:17:47,140 --> 00:17:51,171
I guess Ms. Zheng will say it's internal.

291
00:17:51,171 --> 00:17:53,161
She doesn't have the authority.

292
00:17:57,050 --> 00:18:00,100
Ms. Zheng, C1 is a sophisticated technology

293
00:18:00,100 --> 00:18:03,480
that's been approved many times by our lab.

294
00:18:03,480 --> 00:18:05,760
We already gave full solutions
to the technical issues

295
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:08,140
you raised last time.

296
00:18:09,055 --> 00:18:13,100
Using acceptance failure
as an excuse is ridiculous.

297
00:18:13,100 --> 00:18:15,000
Excuse?

298
00:18:15,000 --> 00:18:16,290
Lin...

299
00:18:16,290 --> 00:18:18,637
Ms. Zheng. How about this?

300
00:18:18,637 --> 00:18:21,310
Could you arrange a meeting
with the technical engineers?

301
00:18:21,310 --> 00:18:22,540
We can discuss this in person.

302
00:18:22,540 --> 00:18:26,466
Even if there's disagreement,
it's probably a misunderstanding.

303
00:18:26,466 --> 00:18:29,371
- We'll work on it.
- I've done my best to fight for you.

304
00:18:29,371 --> 00:18:31,132
But this is the result.

305
00:18:31,132 --> 00:18:33,103
I have to consider the group's interests.

306
00:18:33,103 --> 00:18:34,964
With a decision like that?

307
00:18:34,964 --> 00:18:36,235
Yeah, Ms. Zheng.

308
00:18:36,235 --> 00:18:39,255
You can't give up on such a promising project.

309
00:18:40,271 --> 00:18:42,451
I never said I'd give up.

310
00:18:43,993 --> 00:18:46,684
C1 is indeed a promising project.

311
00:18:46,684 --> 00:18:48,617
No doubt about that.

312
00:18:48,617 --> 00:18:51,728
But the problem is,
you breached the contract first.

313
00:18:51,728 --> 00:18:55,580
You didn't pass the technical acceptance
as agreed.

314
00:18:55,580 --> 00:19:00,565
So, B&amp;C Motors will take over
all of your team's patents and technology.

315
00:19:00,565 --> 00:19:04,406
We'll continue the project
with our internal R&amp;D team.

316
00:19:04,406 --> 00:19:06,630
What did you say?

317
00:19:06,630 --> 00:19:09,495
I think I've made it clear.

318
00:19:09,495 --> 00:19:11,350
You can't just claim it
and make the decision for us.

319
00:19:11,350 --> 00:19:14,840
You can't take away the patents
and tech that we worked hard on.

320
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:20,350
You can keep them if you want.

321
00:19:28,162 --> 00:19:29,480
It's the notice of contract violation.

322
00:19:29,480 --> 00:19:32,230
See if you can accept the amount.

323
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:35,350
Let's go. The discussion's over.

324
00:19:35,350 --> 00:19:36,860
Wait.

325
00:19:36,860 --> 00:19:38,620
How can we just leave?

326
00:19:38,620 --> 00:19:41,900
Who hasn't been beaten down
by life when they were young?

327
00:19:41,900 --> 00:19:43,290
Get used to it.

328
00:19:43,290 --> 00:19:45,020
Young man.

329
00:19:50,350 --> 00:19:52,460
Let's go, Gao Rui.

330
00:19:58,630 --> 00:20:00,110
They just wanna get something for nothing.

331
00:20:00,110 --> 00:20:02,340
B&amp;C Motors was aiming
for our tech patents from the start.

332
00:20:02,340 --> 00:20:03,894
My boyfriend's at the International Law School.

333
00:20:03,894 --> 00:20:06,140
I'll ask him if there's any way to deal with her.

334
00:20:06,140 --> 00:20:08,040
Where's Lin?

335
00:20:10,897 --> 00:20:12,620
You can't find Lin?

336
00:20:12,620 --> 00:20:14,488
None of us can reach him.

337
00:20:14,488 --> 00:20:16,000
Especially Lin Jia Dong.

338
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,180
He has called over ten times in a row.

339
00:20:17,180 --> 00:20:19,760
And now his precious senior
has turned off the phone.

340
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:21,910
Where's my phone?

341
00:20:24,640 --> 00:20:25,968
 

342
00:20:25,968 --> 00:20:27,079
 

343
00:20:27,079 --> 00:20:28,240
 

344
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:29,800
 

345
00:20:41,409 --> 00:20:44,050
A man hit hard in his career is the most fragile.

346
00:20:44,050 --> 00:20:47,690
Everyone's trying to comfort him now.

347
00:20:47,690 --> 00:20:48,900
No way.

348
00:20:48,900 --> 00:20:50,880
He must be working on a solution.

349
00:20:50,880 --> 00:20:53,460
You know him well.

350
00:20:54,110 --> 00:20:55,800
I...

351
00:20:55,800 --> 00:20:58,241
I've been in the lab for years before you.

352
00:20:58,241 --> 00:21:00,121
You know.

353
00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:03,620
So what can he do?

354
00:21:04,630 --> 00:21:06,130
He...

355
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:09,200
He...

356
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:11,420
Honestly, I don't know.

357
00:21:19,740 --> 00:21:21,672
 

358
00:21:21,672 --> 00:21:23,540
 

359
00:21:28,480 --> 00:21:31,179
Every time I see coffee foam poured in,

360
00:21:31,179 --> 00:21:33,779
I think of Olympic diving.

361
00:21:34,442 --> 00:21:36,150
Angle, precision, and strength.

362
00:21:36,150 --> 00:21:37,780
They are all important.

363
00:21:37,780 --> 00:21:42,662
Only then can a simple sport become an art.

364
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:48,441
Impressive.

365
00:21:48,441 --> 00:21:50,180
So what's your plan now?

366
00:21:50,180 --> 00:21:53,010
How do we artistically fight back against B&amp;C?

367
00:21:53,010 --> 00:21:55,270
I don't have a plan, I just will take one step at a time.

368
00:21:55,270 --> 00:21:58,730
Yeah. So, what's your next step?

369
00:21:58,730 --> 00:22:02,220
Isn't going back to the bookstore
part of your plan?

370
00:22:02,880 --> 00:22:06,020
It's just because they're short-handed today.

371
00:22:09,626 --> 00:22:12,626
Do you really have no plan?

372
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:18,790
People in the lab are checking the faults

373
00:22:18,790 --> 00:22:20,640
and reaching out to law students for you.

374
00:22:20,640 --> 00:22:22,790
And you're here acting cool.

375
00:22:22,790 --> 00:22:25,900
Isn't that a bit inappropriate?

376
00:22:25,900 --> 00:22:27,640
One latte.

377
00:22:27,640 --> 00:22:29,300
Okay.

378
00:22:29,300 --> 00:22:31,320
I'm busy, too.

379
00:22:33,350 --> 00:22:35,600
C1 is your years of hard work.

380
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:38,340
Failing this acceptance test could waste all your effort.

381
00:22:38,340 --> 00:22:39,970
And worst of all, the morale is low.

382
00:22:39,970 --> 00:22:42,290
The whole team could fall apart.

383
00:22:43,146 --> 00:22:46,380
We were all stressed out during R&amp;D.

384
00:22:46,380 --> 00:22:50,430
Now's a good time to rest up, including you.

385
00:22:51,350 --> 00:22:52,640
I don't want to rest.

386
00:22:52,640 --> 00:22:54,350
This is not the time to kick back.

387
00:22:54,350 --> 00:22:55,900
You...

388
00:22:57,350 --> 00:22:59,250
Get back to the lab, okay?

389
00:22:59,250 --> 00:23:00,960
I'll cover here.

390
00:23:00,960 --> 00:23:02,860
Back to the lab. Give me your apron.

391
00:23:02,860 --> 00:23:04,780
Too many customers.

392
00:23:04,780 --> 00:23:06,620
Can't leave.

393
00:23:18,590 --> 00:23:20,560
Hi, Shu Lan?

394
00:23:22,260 --> 00:23:24,780
 

395
00:23:31,680 --> 00:23:33,190
Xue Jiao.

396
00:23:33,960 --> 00:23:36,410
This is Lawyer Zhang.
Also an alumnus of Capital University.

397
00:23:36,410 --> 00:23:39,750
My boyfriend says he's got a ton of experience
with cases like this.

398
00:23:39,750 --> 00:23:41,540
- Nice to meet you, Mr. Zhang.
- Nice to meet you, too.

399
00:23:41,540 --> 00:23:43,830
I already filled him in on the basics.

400
00:23:43,830 --> 00:23:46,710
You talk about the rest.

401
00:23:47,240 --> 00:23:49,240
Mr. Zhang, have a seat.

402
00:23:53,350 --> 00:23:55,154
So, based on the current situation,

403
00:23:55,154 --> 00:23:58,060
do we stand a good chance?

404
00:23:58,060 --> 00:24:02,480
Sounds like B&amp;C's bet-on agreement
has some nasty clauses.

405
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:05,750
If we push from that angle, we might have a shot.

406
00:24:05,750 --> 00:24:07,270
Great.

407
00:24:07,270 --> 00:24:09,650
But their legal team is pretty tough.

408
00:24:09,650 --> 00:24:11,410
It could get messy.

409
00:24:11,410 --> 00:24:14,580
And going to court won't be cheap.

410
00:24:14,580 --> 00:24:15,780
I understand.

411
00:24:15,780 --> 00:24:18,300
May I ask, how do you charge?

412
00:24:18,300 --> 00:24:20,391
For corporate commercial disputes,

413
00:24:20,391 --> 00:24:23,620
we usually charge
a percentage of the claim amount.

414
00:24:23,620 --> 00:24:25,170
Since my junior referred you,

415
00:24:25,170 --> 00:24:26,960
I'll cut you a little slack.

416
00:24:26,960 --> 00:24:30,750
But probably not under 5%.

417
00:24:30,750 --> 00:24:33,210
5%...

418
00:24:33,210 --> 00:24:35,850
That's fine. You can think it over.

419
00:24:37,880 --> 00:24:39,530
Wait a sec.

420
00:24:43,400 --> 00:24:47,800
 Tian Tian, your idea investor needs cash now. 

421
00:24:48,920 --> 00:24:51,898
No problem. We're taking this to court.

422
00:24:51,898 --> 00:24:57,010
 Last time, Ms. Zheng from B&amp;C took C1 from me. 

423
00:24:57,010 --> 00:25:01,140
 This time, I'm fighting back. 

424
00:25:02,520 --> 00:25:03,680
Sorry, Mr. Zhao.

425
00:25:03,680 --> 00:25:05,110
Thank you for waiting.

426
00:25:05,110 --> 00:25:07,590
No worries.

427
00:25:07,590 --> 00:25:09,730
I just invested in a new mobile game.

428
00:25:09,730 --> 00:25:11,620
It's pretty fun.

429
00:25:11,620 --> 00:25:13,000
Level 88 in one swing.

430
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:14,310
If you're my bro, come slash me.

431
00:25:14,310 --> 00:25:15,400
Kinda entertaining.

432
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,270
Is it?

433
00:25:18,480 --> 00:25:20,210
Interesting.

434
00:25:20,210 --> 00:25:26,200
Lin, I heard your C1 project with B&amp;C hasn't been going too smoothly.

435
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,445
Mr. Zhao, do you remember

436
00:25:30,445 --> 00:25:32,246
B&amp;C's very first locally-developed model

437
00:25:32,246 --> 00:25:37,550
when they made a high-profile entry
into the Chinese market 20 years ago?

438
00:25:37,550 --> 00:25:39,350
It's been too long.

439
00:25:39,350 --> 00:25:41,910
Can't really recall. Sorry.

440
00:25:44,550 --> 00:25:46,340
I do.

441
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:50,060
I remember it because it was developed

442
00:25:50,060 --> 00:25:52,490
by one of our Capital University alumni

443
00:25:52,490 --> 00:25:56,000
leading an on-campus R&amp;D team.

444
00:25:57,944 --> 00:25:59,590
You checked my background?

445
00:25:59,590 --> 00:26:01,900
I only just found out.

446
00:26:03,650 --> 00:26:08,680
Turns out you're a cautionary tale
for my cooperation with B&amp;C.

447
00:26:08,680 --> 00:26:10,285
Senior Zhao.

448
00:26:10,285 --> 00:26:14,806
Lin, I told you, if it's not about making money,

449
00:26:14,806 --> 00:26:16,087
I'm not interested.

450
00:26:16,087 --> 00:26:18,728
So let's call it a day.

451
00:26:18,728 --> 00:26:20,198
Mr. Zhao,

452
00:26:21,071 --> 00:26:27,635
that model you built
got its funding cut before delivery.

453
00:26:27,635 --> 00:26:29,480
Do you still have dreams?

454
00:26:29,480 --> 00:26:34,400
At this age, isn't it kinda corny to have dreams?

455
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:38,400
But you keep going to automotive
industry investment conferences.

456
00:26:38,400 --> 00:26:40,765
It's pretty obvious.

457
00:26:40,765 --> 00:26:42,955
Otherwise, we wouldn't have met.

458
00:26:43,590 --> 00:26:48,710
I was the first one to show interest in your C1 project.

459
00:26:48,710 --> 00:26:50,615
But you?

460
00:26:51,750 --> 00:26:55,510
You turned your back on my Junlian Company

461
00:26:55,510 --> 00:26:58,150
and shook hands with B&amp;C.

462
00:26:59,070 --> 00:27:03,311
It's hard to explain my beef with B&amp;C for now.

463
00:27:03,311 --> 00:27:08,450
But C1's failing delivery
was part of my plan all along.

464
00:27:15,790 --> 00:27:17,315
What are you doing?

465
00:27:17,315 --> 00:27:19,476
Who told you to move our lab's equipment?

466
00:27:19,476 --> 00:27:21,466
Hey, I'm talking to you!

467
00:27:22,160 --> 00:27:23,790
Did you hear me?

468
00:27:23,790 --> 00:27:27,910
Dude, what are you talking about?

469
00:27:27,910 --> 00:27:29,820
Since when are they yours?

470
00:27:29,820 --> 00:27:32,680
They belong to B&amp;C Motors now.

471
00:27:32,680 --> 00:27:34,110
We can sponsor you.

472
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:36,270
And we can take it back, too. Right?

473
00:27:36,270 --> 00:27:38,380
Even if B&amp;C Motors sponsored it,

474
00:27:38,380 --> 00:27:41,270
we're just fulfilling the terms of our contract.

475
00:27:41,270 --> 00:27:43,070
Can you at least honor the contract?

476
00:27:43,070 --> 00:27:44,900
You can't just take it back whenever you want.

477
00:27:44,900 --> 00:27:46,310
That contract is off now.

478
00:27:46,310 --> 00:27:49,000
Ms. Zheng only recognizes
the notice of contract violation.

479
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:51,160
Okay. Enough talk.

480
00:27:51,160 --> 00:27:52,350
Sign it.

481
00:27:52,350 --> 00:27:53,860
Hurry.

482
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:11,620
They...

483
00:28:12,540 --> 00:28:15,180
they basically moved everything.

484
00:28:18,420 --> 00:28:21,760
 

485
00:28:26,540 --> 00:28:29,730
What's your plan against B&amp;C?

486
00:28:29,730 --> 00:28:32,890
I want them gone from China for good.

487
00:28:33,720 --> 00:28:35,350
You?

488
00:28:40,121 --> 00:28:41,162
What a surprise.

489
00:28:41,162 --> 00:28:44,830
College kids today are crazier than we used to be.

490
00:28:44,830 --> 00:28:50,660
Lin, working with B&amp;C Motors
isn't some kid's play.

491
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:53,401
This is against investor ethics,

492
00:28:53,401 --> 00:28:55,780
but I gotta remind you.

493
00:28:55,780 --> 00:29:01,770
No tech team working with B&amp;C Motors
ever ends well.

494
00:29:04,550 --> 00:29:10,340
So I'm here today
to ask for your original contract

495
00:29:10,340 --> 00:29:12,720
and the termination agreement back then.

496
00:29:17,817 --> 00:29:19,747
 On my way home. 

497
00:29:20,830 --> 00:29:24,820
 Stop making coffee and just gonna stay in, huh? 

498
00:29:24,820 --> 00:29:29,180
 Lin Zhi Hua, wait till I come over and get you. 

499
00:29:29,180 --> 00:29:33,220
 

500
00:29:56,240 --> 00:29:58,160
Do you know how long we waited for you today?

501
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:00,700
Even the lab gear got taken by B&amp;C Motors.

502
00:30:02,240 --> 00:30:04,670
Sit down first. Don't be mad.

503
00:30:07,440 --> 00:30:08,650
I know.

504
00:30:08,650 --> 00:30:11,210
I'm just trying to chill a bit.

505
00:30:11,210 --> 00:30:12,780
Mr. Zhao told me about this game.

506
00:30:12,780 --> 00:30:14,690
It's fun. Very addictive. Look.

507
00:30:14,690 --> 00:30:17,980
Are you seriously playing games
at a time like this?

508
00:30:22,240 --> 00:30:23,310
I asked you to meet with the lawyer.

509
00:30:23,310 --> 00:30:24,990
Why didn't you come?

510
00:30:25,750 --> 00:30:27,600
I was gaming.

511
00:30:28,720 --> 00:30:30,400
Ten o'clock tomorrow morning.

512
00:30:30,400 --> 00:30:31,780
Come with me to see the lawyer.

513
00:30:31,780 --> 00:30:33,170
I already paid the fees.

514
00:30:33,170 --> 00:30:37,170
If you don't, you're gonna get it.

515
00:30:37,170 --> 00:30:38,790
Get what?

516
00:30:38,790 --> 00:30:41,210
Stop joking around.

517
00:30:45,270 --> 00:30:48,090
First things first.

518
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:54,347
I know this is tough, but running away won't help.

519
00:30:54,347 --> 00:30:55,540
Don't worry.

520
00:30:55,540 --> 00:30:57,001
No matter how hard it is,

521
00:30:57,001 --> 00:30:59,882
I'll be with you through it all.

522
00:30:59,882 --> 00:31:01,422
Okay.

523
00:31:02,254 --> 00:31:04,094
If you say so.

524
00:31:06,960 --> 00:31:08,210
When?

525
00:31:08,210 --> 00:31:10,570
Ten o'clock tomorrow morning.

526
00:31:32,240 --> 00:31:33,900
Gao Rui?

527
00:31:35,790 --> 00:31:37,720
What a coincidence. You're off work?

528
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:40,380
I'm just taking a walk nearby.

529
00:31:40,380 --> 00:31:42,180
Happened to walk by.

530
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:44,910
Yeah.

531
00:31:45,640 --> 00:31:49,490
You walked here all the way
from Capital University?

532
00:31:49,490 --> 00:31:51,490
That's a long walk.

533
00:31:54,680 --> 00:31:56,550
Right. Are you available later?

534
00:31:56,550 --> 00:32:00,110
Let me buy you dinner.

535
00:32:20,960 --> 00:32:23,800
Do you want one more bottle?

536
00:32:25,921 --> 00:32:27,132
Okay.

537
00:32:27,132 --> 00:32:30,062
Are you still not going to tell me?

538
00:32:32,152 --> 00:32:34,340
You were here to see me, right?

539
00:32:34,340 --> 00:32:36,930
Just say what you want to say.

540
00:32:40,540 --> 00:32:45,250
I... I do have something to tell you.

541
00:32:50,959 --> 00:32:52,559
I...

542
00:32:53,350 --> 00:32:54,870
I...

543
00:32:59,180 --> 00:33:00,270
- Excuse me! 
